ssword has 26^6 = approximately 309 million possible combinations. An 8-character password has 26^8 = approximately 209 billion combinations. A 12-character password has 26^12 = approximately 95 trillion combinations. Add uppercase letters, numbers and symbols and the combinations become astronomical.</p> <p>Modern computers can attempt billions of password guesses per second. A 6-character lowercase password can be cracked in seconds. A 12-character password with mixed characters would take thousands of years even with the most powerful computers available today. Our generator supports passwords up to 50 characters — at that length with all character types enabled, no computer that has ever been built or ever will be built could crack it by brute force within the lifetime of the universe.</p> </div> <div class="seo-block"> <h2>⚠️ How Hackers Crack Passwords — The Main Attack Methods</h2> <div class="threat-grid"> <div class="threat-card"><div class="tc-icon">💻</div><div class="tc-title">Brute Force Attack</div><div class="tc-desc">Systematically tries every possible combination. Effective against short passwords — ineffe
